==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harper
<hw>Harp"er</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rp"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>hearpere</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A player on the harp; a
minstrel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The murmuring pines and the hemlocks . . . ⟦br⟧
Stand like <qex>harpers</qex> hoar, with beards that rest on their
bosoms.</q> <rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A brass coin bearing the emblem of a harp, --
formerly current in Ireland.</def> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harping</ent>⟦br⟧
